Pooled effects of continuous variables will be expressed as Morris’s delta (Morris’s dppc), if the same primary outcomes are used in the eligible studies. Morris described a pre-post control effect size as “the mean pre-post change in the treatment group minus the mean pre-post change in the control group, divided by the pooled baseline standard deviation of both the treatment and control groups” [75, 76]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
